5:
So that cryptic artifact that was
creating all the sheep suddenly
stopped working?
9:
Yeah. It was definitely converting
people's feelings into energy and
then using it to create sheep, but...
12:
It looks like the artifact's internal
mechanisms were damaged by
excessive output. I think it was
probably something akin to a
prototype.
19:
Oh, n-never mind! Do you want to
go out for a bite to eat in a little
while?
25:
A power outage? That's... highly
unusual...
42:
We tried using ice magic to stop a
rampaging golem, but we went a
little overboard and... caused a
power outage in the building.
44:
Your door is currently frozen shut,
but don't worry. We'll get you out of
there as soon as we can.
55:
Then that means... In this dark room,
we're...
67:
...Th-the power's been out for a
while, huh?
75:
Wh-why won't you let me get close
to you, Will?
79:
I-it's not that I've got anything
against you, Mary! It's just... It's dark,
and I don't want to make you
uncomfortable.
83:
I'm not uncomfortable, Will! I'm with
you! You could take a little more
initiative sometimes, you know?
85:
Like with holding hands! I'm always
grabbing your hand, but you almost
never grab mine...
92:
I'm worried you'll stop liking me if I'm
too aggressive...
98:
...Wow. So we've been thinking the
same thing, then.
101:
I made up my mind to honestly tell
you how I feel. But I might still be a
little afraid after all...
105: Me too. It's just like the sheep said...
108:
I'm afraid of pushing you away, so I
thought maybe it was best to just
do nothing...
111:
But as scared as I might be... I need
you to know that I love you.
114:
M-more than anything in the world,
I...
121:
I worry about a future where you
might not like me anymore... And
yet, I can't imagine a future where I
stop loving you.
124:
Um... Will? I've got something I want
to say, too...
138:
My heart's making so much noise
right now...
142:
That makes me happy, Will... To
know that's how you feel.
144:
There's still so much I want to know
about you...
153: And we got it! It's open now—
156:
...We fixed the power outage, too. It's
late, so you two need to head home.
159:
I bet you're glad it wasn't Professor
Leleni who walked in on you, huh?
165:
...F-food, that's right! Let's go get
some food!
180:
I-I'm going to head home now! See
you later!
198: Sorry to keep you waiting, everyone—
208:
Really? Y-you did it ON campus?!
Have you no SHAME?
218:
All right, Mary. Time to stop
pretending and tell us all the details.
220:
Since it's Mary we're talking about,
it's safe to assume she lost her cool
and just went down on—
250: G-give me a break, you guys!
